 Purpose

Move Oracle tablespace files between diskgroups and reset init.ora parameters.

 Description

When using DBCA with ASM, all files and init.ora parameters that reference disk locations are all directed to the diskgroup specified by the diskGroupName parameter. This undesirable behavior overrides the diskgroup specifications in the template file.
This workflow is designed to move individual files or all files in a tablespace to the specified diskgroup.
Any init.ora parameters specified will be executed using the command "alter system set  scope\=both".

 Required Inputs

    Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
    Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
    Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
    Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
    Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
    Diskgroup - The name of the ASM diskgroup the specified tablespaces and/or files will be moved to.
    Files - Comma separated list of files and/or tablespace to move to the specified diskgroup.
    Instance.Name - No description
    Oracle Account - Required\: The user who owns ORACLE_HOME.
    Server.Become Routine - No description

 Optional Inputs

    Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
    Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
    Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
    Init Parameters - Optional\: Comma separated list of init.ora parameters to apply to an active database.

 Dependencies

\# On Unix only, the workflow must have the unchallenged ability to become the software owner (typically "oracle").



 Additional Documentation

Additional information, including the _HP Database and Middleware Automation Support Matrix_ and solution pack user guides, are available via HP Live Network\:

"http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation"\:http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation

To access the documentation, click the RESOURCES link and enter your HP Passport credentials.
